import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['normal'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.8)
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['normal'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['normal'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_datetime(data['actual'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='day')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['day'], data['forecast'], label='Forecasted Temperature')
    ax.plot(data['day'], data['actual'], label='Actual Temperature')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('How does the actual temperature compare to the forecasted temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['difference'] = pd.to_datetime(data['difference'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['difference'].dt.total_seconds() / 3600, vert=False, widths=0.7, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'), whiskerprops=dict(color='black'), capprops=dict(color='black'))
    ax.set_xlabel('Hours')
    ax.set_yticklabels(['Difference'])
    ax.axvline(data['difference'].dt.total_seconds().mean() / 3600, color='red', label=f'Mean: {data["difference"].dt.total_seconds().mean() / 3600:.2f} hours')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average difference between the actual and forecasted temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['difference'] = pd.to_datetime(data['difference'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['difference'] = data['difference'].dt.days
    plt.hist(data['difference'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['difference'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['difference'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Difference between actual and forecasted temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_datetime(data['actual'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['difference'] = data['actual'] - data['forecast']
    data = data.sort_values(by='day')
    plt.plot(data['day'], data['difference'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['difference'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.title('How does the difference between the actual and forecasted temperature vary over time?')
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature Difference')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
